This paper discusses the comparison of two academic literature databases, which are commonly used in computer science research. The paper focuses on the qualitative and quantitative characteristics of these databases, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The paper's content is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, the paper's primary focus is on digital libraries and information retrieval, making cs.DL and cs.IR the most likely sub-categories.
